 {"id":"bd-3uqg.10.4","title":"[PROVIDER-ROLLUP] Completion handoff package + remaining-gap beads","description":"Prepare final handoff package with what shipped, what is deferred, operational risks, and exact next beads to pick up remaining gaps. Include thread links, test evidence, and provider matrix diff summary so the next agent can continue without re-deriving context. This closes the loop on the self-contained planning objective.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Completion handoff includes shipped/deferred scope, ownership, and linked unit plus e2e evidence artifacts for every provider family. 2) Handoff bundle includes structured log/transcript indexes, parity audit references, and unresolved-risk register with follow-up beads. 3) Next-agent bootstrap steps are executable end-to-end without rereading historical planning docs.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:21:08.011473796Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T03:09:04.010023612Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.10.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.10","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:21:08.011473796Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.10.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.10.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:50.442871173Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.10.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.8.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:50.832311145Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.10.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.9.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T02:22:50.636345213Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3uqg.11","title":"[PROVIDER-GAPS] Missing provider completion wave (Groq, Cerebras, OpenRouter, Kimi, Qwen + upstream deltas)","description":"User-reported gap: despite prior provider-parity waves, major providers expected from opencode and the code ecosystem are still missing from runtime truth. This wave closes that delta with an explicit, evidence-first plan focused on named providers (Groq, Cerebras, OpenRouter, Kimi, Qwen) and any additional upstream misses discovered in a fresh catalog diff.\\n\\nIntent:\\n- Remove ambiguity between planning artifacts and shipping code by making this subtree the source of truth.\\n- Sequence work so shared architecture/auth decisions happen once, then provider implementations execute in parallel safely.\\n- Ensure each provider reaches implementation + tests + docs + operational evidence (not partial onboarding).\\n\\nScope:\\n- In scope: provider metadata/routing, auth/env contracts, stream normalization, model registry alignment, provider-specific tests, e2e smoke/failure cases, docs and troubleshooting.\\n- Out of scope: speculative providers not present in upstream frozen catalogs unless added through explicit diff evidence.","design":"Design principle: use shared-core tasks for routing/auth/test harness before provider-specific slices to reduce duplicate churn and cross-provider drift. Providers that are OpenAI-compatible by transport still require explicit normalization/auth/model-contract decisions because error surfaces and tool-call semantics diverge by vendor.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Fresh upstream diff artifact explicitly lists missing providers and status for each (implemented / mapped / deferred) with evidence links. 2) Groq, Cerebras, OpenRouter, Kimi, and Qwen each have completed implementation, provider-specific tests, and docs/troubleshooting entries. 3) Dependency graph in this subtree is acyclic and executable by multiple agents in parallel. 4) Final rollup bead provides closure evidence sufficient to avoid consulting older markdown plans.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:04.999695548Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:11.256529489Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.11","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:04.999695548Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3uqg.11.1","title":"[PROVIDER-GAPS-SPEC] Recompute canonical upstream provider diff (opencode + code catalogs)","description":"Produce a fresh, frozen diff between current Pi provider surface and upstream reference ecosystems (opencode + code). This is the grounding artifact for all implementation decisions in this subtree.\\n\\nDeliverables:\\n- Machine-readable matrix with columns: provider_id, canonical_aliases, expected_api_family, auth_scheme, tool-call support expectations, current_pi_status, target_status.\\n- Explicit inclusion of user-called-out providers (Groq, Cerebras, OpenRouter, Kimi, Qwen) plus any additional discovered deltas.\\n- Risk tags: high (user-visible gap), medium (partial parity), low (nice-to-have).","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:31.615997500Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:31.615997500Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3uqg.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3uqg.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T04:15:31.615997500Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
